-- 
Hungary Plans to Cut Budget Deficit in 2012, 2013, Outline Shows

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-07-19T15:16:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/hungary-plans-to-cut-budget-deficit-in-2012-2013-outline-shows.html
Hungary plans to cut its fiscal
deficit next year and in 2013, according to the first outline of
the budget published in the Official Gazette.  The cash-flow budget deficit excluding municipalities may
total 606 billion forint ($3.2 billion) in 2012 and 594 billion
forint in 2013, compared with the original target of 687 billion
forint this year, according to government figures published in
the  Official Gazette  yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  